title: For Sale:  JLD Enterprises, Inc. PTR 91 (H&K 91 G3)
postcontent:
The PTR 91 is an American made "clone" of the famous H&K 91 G3 rifles. After H&K stopped production of their 91 rifles, clones popped up on the market made out of surplus parts and cheap assembly, therefore PTR started production of the famous H&K 91 rifles by recieving the blueprints straight from their German source.

It comes with an original H&K retracting stock, H&K full stock and forearm. Also comes with a UTG picatinny tri-rail forearm, bipod, weaver scope mount and a total of 40 H&K magazines, 39 are 20 round mags and one original 5 round magazine.

Rifle is new and in excellent condition. I have only shot 40 rounds down the barrel, it has an adjustable rear sight and a fixed front sight. I will also throw in the Technical Manual & Armorer's Course from the American Gunsmithing Institute for the H&K 91 G-3 Rifles. In order to take care of your rifle, one must understand how it works first.

Check out the You tube video of the PTR 91 for yourself: http: //youtu.be/ctyKezaegds

title: For Trade:  1934 izzy mosin
postcontent:
Nagants in good enough shape to be salvaged were part of the soviets massive refurbishment program following ww2. The primary reasons behind the huge post war overhaul of large, obsolete rifle stockpiles were the anticipation of another impending world war, and the plan to call up seasoned veterans in defense of the motherland. Already familiar with their old mosin nagant rifles and revolvers, those veterans would likely have required very little new training and would easily and rapidly reintegrate into the red machine. 
With the development of newer semi auots that would have required extensive massive retraining, the important issue became of quick mobilization became apearant. However time passed and those great ww2 veterans eventually aged beyond the point of viability. While newer weapons took over the worlds battlefields, the stocks of long outdated ordnance were now imported to the USA. 

This is a pre war 1934 izzy manufacture m90/31 with hexagonal reciever with original russian laminate non refurbished stock. This rifles bore is stone mint shiny chromed out! "Have neer seen one like this" The metal has not a mark on it is stone mint! The magazine follower, action etc have no wear! Mint bore. All matching. No refurbishment marks from other countrys on the stock.
This is a very early import that was sold wrapped in brown paper tied in twine. This rifle saw little to no action its entire life, maybe an officers or political gaurds weapon

The rifles antiquated lines, and historical signifigance is something to be sought after for years to come. This rifle was made well when an individuals workmanship was apreciated and one took pride in what they did. It also was a matter of national pride, a "we made it here" battle rifle.

will trade for a tokarev pistol

email call text REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Not found in retail stores! Factory shorter barrel & upgrades: competition compensator pinned to Adams Arms 14.5" Evo Ultra Lite Gas Piston Upper Receiver Assembly with Competition Compensator
postcontent:
Brand New in Box! This Adams Arms EVO Ultra Lite Mid Length Gas Piston Upper Assembly is chambered in 5.56x45mm NATO and comes ready to fire right out of the box after installation onto any AR-15 pistol lower receiver. Designed to be the ultimate lightweight solution for competitive, recreational or hunting purposes, the EVO Ultra Lite trims weight wherever possible while still maintaining excellent accuracy, long term durability and high performance. It does this by combining a melonite treated, 14.5" ultra-light contour barrel with a 12" extended Samson Evolution Modular Free Floating Handguard and a low profile piston gas block. The shooter's preferred sighting arrangement is easily accommodated by a continuous top picatinny rail interface that runs from the rear of the forged A3 flat-top upper receiver to the low profile gas block, while both recoil and muzzle climb are efficiently handled by an effective Adams Arms Competition Compensator. Additional features include a mid length gas system for a longer sight radius and smoother recoil impulse, complete bolt carrier group, charging handle assembly, one 4" modular rail section and two 2" rail sections. 

The upper's barrel has been finished inside and out with Adams Arms' proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment that bonds with the metal on a molecular level. Also referred to as salt bath nitriding, this treatment produces an extremely hard, slick surface on steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion resistance, extending a barrel's service life by reducing the friction produced inside the bore upon firing for a net decrease in bore surface wear over time. Nitriding converts the barrel steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered due to uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore. The end result is a barrel that's capable of producing accuracy on par with a match stainless steel tube, while also exhibiting the longevity and resilience of a chrome lined, mil-spec barrel. 

All Adams Arms uppers feature a short stroke gas piston operating system, which prevents hot gas and debris from being directed back into the action upon firing. The result is a rifle that runs cooler, cleaner and more reliably than those utilizing a standard direct gas impingement system of operation. To ensure that damage doesn't occur to the buffer tube from carrier tilt, the bolt carrier is equipped with enlarged "skis" to help guide it into the receiver extension. The bolt carrier's solid steel, 1-piece construction incorporates an integral piston strike face to guarantee integrity over time, while the bolt assembly is spring loaded for proper lock-up and to help reduce bolt bounce and cam pin wear. All piston components are finished in QPQ Melonite for corrosion resistance and easy cleaning/maintenance. 

Technical Information
Upper Receiver Type: A3 Flat-Top, Forged
Barrel Length: 14.5" Pistol
Barrel Contour: Ultra Lightweight
Barrel Material:4150 Chrome Moly Vanadium Steel
Muzzle Thread Pattern: 1/2"-28
Chrome Lined: No
Barrel Finish: QPQ Melonite / Black Nitride
Twist Rate: 1 in 7"
Chamber: 5.56x45mm NATO
M4 Feed Ramps: Yes
Muzzle Device: Adams Arms Compensator
Gas System Length: Mid-length, short stroke piston operated
Gas Block Diameter: 0.625"
Handguard: Samson 12" Evolution Extended Modular Rail, Free Float
Sights: None
Extras: Two 2" and one 4" Picatinny Rail Sections
